{
  "local_port": 45890,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can one use Bootstrap?",
  "response": "Bootstrap is a popular front-end framework that helps developers create responsive and mobile-first websites quickly and efficiently. Here\u2019s how you can use Bootstrap:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Include Bootstrap in Your Project**\nThere are several ways to include Bootstrap in your project:\n\n#### **Option 1: Use a CDN (Content Delivery Network)**\nAdd the following links to the `<head>` section of your HTML file for Bootstrap CSS and JavaScript:\n\n```html\n<!-- Bootstrap CSS -->\n<link \n  href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css\" \n  rel=\"stylesheet\" \n  integrity=\"sha384-<hash>\" \n  crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n\n<!-- Bootstrap JS and Popper.js (for interactive components) -->\n<script \n  src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\" \n  integrity=\"sha384-<hash>\" \n  crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n</script>\n```\n\n#### **Option 2: Download and Use Locally**\n- [Download Bootstrap](https://getbootstrap.com/) from the official website.\n- Extract the files and include the `bootstrap.min.css` and `bootstrap.bundle.min.js` files in your project.\n\n```html\n<!-- Local Bootstrap CSS -->\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"path/to/bootstrap.min.css\">\n\n<!-- Local Bootstrap JS -->\n<script src=\"path/to/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n```\n\n#### **Option 3: Install via Package Managers**\nYou can install Bootstrap using npm, yarn, or other package managers:\n\n```bash\nnpm install bootstrap\n```\n\nThen, import it in your JavaScript or CSS files:\n\n```javascript\nimport 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';\nimport 'bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Start Using Bootstrap Components**\nBootstrap provides pre-styled components such as buttons, navbars, cards, modals, and more. Here\u2019s an example of using a button:\n\n```html\n<button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">Primary Button</button>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Use the Grid System**\nBootstrap\u2019s grid system is based on a 12-column layout. You can create responsive layouts using classes like `row` and `col`:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"container\">\n  <div class=\"row\">\n    <div class=\"col-md-6\">Column 1</div>\n    <div class=\"col-md-6\">Column 2</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Customize Bootstrap**\nYou can customize Bootstrap by overriding its default variables. For example, create a custom CSS file and override variables:\n\n```css\n:root {\n  --bs-primary: #ff0000; /* Change primary color to red */\n}\n```\n\nOr, use the [Sass version of Bootstrap](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/getting-started/download/#npm) to customize the source files.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Explore Documentation**\nRefer to the [official Bootstrap documentation](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/) for detailed examples, components, and utilities.\n\n---\n\n### Example: Basic Bootstrap HTML Template\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>Bootstrap Example</title>\n  <link \n    href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css\" \n    rel=\"stylesheet\" \n    integrity=\"sha384-<hash>\" \n    crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <h1 class=\"text-center\">Hello, Bootstrap!</h1>\n    <button type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-success\">Click Me</button>\n  </div>\n  <script \n    src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\" \n    integrity=\"sha384-<hash>\" \n    crossorigin=\"anonymous\">\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nThis is a basic guide to get started with Bootstrap. Explore the framework to leverage its full potential!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
